Project Overview:
This project applies the Markowitz portfolio optimization approach to evaluate different investment allocation strategies. 
The analysis compares portfolio performance under both hypothetical conditions and a stable market environment while considering the trade-off between risk and expected return.

Tools:
- Microsoft Excel
- Financial Analysis
- Portfolio Optimization
- Risk Assessment
Methods Applied:
- Markowitz portfolio theory
- Expected return calculation
- Risk estimation using variance and standard deviation
- Portfolio diversification analysis
- Comparison of alternative investment allocations
- Risk-return evaluation

Results:
The project demonstrates how portfolio diversification influences investment performance and risk exposure. 
Different allocation scenarios are compared to identify more efficient investment strategies and to support informed financial decision-making.
